# Hospital Management Data Analytics | Excel Project

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates the application of Microsoft Excel for data analysis using a hospital management use case.  
It focuses on data cleaning, exploratory analysis, KPI tracking, and dashboard creation to support data-driven decision making.

---

## Key Objectives
- Analyze patient admission and discharge trends  
- Evaluate department-wise operational performance  
- Perform hospital revenue and billing analysis  
- Identify inefficiencies using length-of-stay metrics  
- Build an interactive Excel dashboard for insights  

---

## Tools & Skills
- Microsoft Excel  
- Pivot Tables & Pivot Charts  
- Excel Functions: SUMIFS, COUNTIFS, IF, IFERROR, XLOOKUP  
- Data Cleaning & Validation  
- Date & Time Analysis  
- Dashboard Design with Slicers  

---

## Dataset Summary
Simulated hospital dataset containing:
- Patient demographics and admission details  
- Department and doctor information  
- Billing, charges, and payment modes  

---

## Analysis Performed
- Patient volume analysis by month and department  
- Revenue contribution by department  
- Average length of stay (LOS) analysis  
- Gender and age group distribution  
- Peak admission period identification  

---

## Dashboard Features
- KPIs: Total Patients, Total Revenue, Average Length of Stay  
- Department-wise patient and revenue charts  
- Interactive filters for department and time period  

---

## Key Outcomes
- Improved understanding of healthcare data analytics  
- Strong foundation in Excel-based analysis workflows  
- Ability to translate raw data into actionable business insights  

---

